```latex
\begin{proof}
Let $x\in\mathbb{R}$. Let $y\in\mathbb{R}$. Assume $x > 0$. Assume $y > 0$. We have $(\sqrt{x} - \sqrt{y})^2 \ge 0$. We have $x - 2\sqrt{xy} + y = (\sqrt{x} - \sqrt{y})^2 \ge 0$. We have $x+y \ge 2\sqrt{xy}$. We have $\frac{x+y}{2} \ge \sqrt{xy}$.
\end{proof}
